{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"93d348c2-9018-4bfb-be16-65194455f190","agentId":"ac7412ffbec86d0e3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Design an implementation plan for a greenfield React web application - a Warcraft 3 Build Order Helper. The repo is currently empty at /home/garrosh/repos/wc3-react.\n\n## Requirements:\n1. **Frontend**: React with JSX, Redux for state management\n2. **Backend**: Node.js with Express (REST API)\n3. **Database**: PostgreSQL\n4. **Core Feature**: Build order timer/counter that plays sounds at build order timestamps (e.g., \"2:50min upgrade to tech tier 2\")\n5. **Races**: Support all 4 WC3 races: Human, Orc, Undead, Night Elf\n6. **Build Orders**: Users can input custom build orders OR pick from premade ones\n7. **Usage**: Designed for a side monitor while playing WC3\n\n## Design considerations:\n- This is a learning project (React, Redux, Node, Postgres, Web APIs)\n- The timer needs to be precise and play audio cues at specific timestamps\n- Web Audio API or HTML5 Audio for sound playback\n- Build orders consist of timed steps: timestamp, action (build unit, upgrade, etc.)\n- UI should be compact/vertical for side monitor use\n- The user wants to learn these technologies, so use them properly (not shortcuts)\n\n## Please design:\n1. Project structure (monorepo with client/ and server/ or separate)\n2. Database schema (tables for races, build orders, build order steps)\n3. API endpoints (CRUD for build orders)\n4. Frontend architecture (components, Redux store shape, pages/routes)\n5. Timer mechanism (how to handle precise audio playback at timestamps)\n6. Tech stack specifics (which versions, bundler, etc.)\n7. Step-by-step implementation order (what to build first)\n\nKeep it practical and focused on learning. Suggest a modern but not overly complex setup (e.g., Create React App or Vite for scaffolding)."},"uuid":"06281441-6ab6-4f2f-8e22-3d84b0e39f01","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:46:25.322Z","userType"